                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18231203-97-victim951 t18231203-97-viclabel516"></join>. On the 12th of November, about eleven o'clock in the morning, I was in the parlour, behind the shop, heard a noise, turned round, and saw the prisoner going out. I followed, and collared him, with the hat in his hand, on the otherside of the way.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. Was I not intoxicated - A. Not to my knowledge.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I certainly was intoxicated, and the hat was put into my hand by some boys.</p>
